      "value": "<h3><img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbolN.gif\" title=\"The muddling heresy poison is only available for use with the boons on page 73.\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\"> Muddling heresy</h3><p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Pathfinder #107: Scourge of the Godclaw pg. 73</em></p><p><strong>Price</strong> 750 gp; <strong>Weight</strong> 0</p><p><strong>Type</strong> injury; <strong>Save</strong> Fortitude DC 20</p><p><strong>Frequency</strong> 1/round for 6 rounds</p><p><strong>Effect</strong> 1d4+1 Wis damage</p><p><strong>Cure</strong> 2 saves</p><h4 class=\"framing\"><strong>Description</strong><h4><p>The poison muddling heresy is often used by worshipers of Geryon to make others more susceptible to being convinced of blasphemies and revelations of heretical truths. While the poison can be used on its own, when used as part of a deific boon, the save DC, duration, or other effects may differ from normal.</p>",
